<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>get the wind up • raise the wind</xh5><p> <i>get the wind up</i>—<i>(sl.)</i> become nervous or scared <i>(also: get the breeze up): </i>I happened to see his face in the mirror as I went out. He’s <u>got the wind up</u> all right.</p><p> <i>raise the wind</i>—(coll.) obtain money, especially by borrowing: He came to me this morning to <u>raise the wind</u>.</p> </entry>
